<p><strong>Assignment</strong></p>

<p>Open the file
<a href="http://qrc.depaul.edu/Excel_Files/Chicago/ChicagoData.xls">
ChicagoData.xls</a> which contains a variety of data about Chicago: population, 
crime, age distribution. You can
navigate from sheet to sheet by clicking on the tabs at the bottom of the screen. Your
task is to make a PowerPoint presentation summarizing this data.&nbsp;  </p>

<p>Requirements:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Title slide with group members' names.</li>
  <li>At least 5 slides with data. <strong>Note: </strong>in most cases you need 
  to make calculations in Excel in order to put the data into &quot;presentation 
  shape&quot;, that is to make the data meaningful. Choose your chart types 
  carefully.</li>
  <li>Concluding slide</li>
  <li>At least one image of Chicago.&nbsp; One starting point for finding images 
  is the the City of Chicago website <a href="http://www.ci.chi.il.us/">
  http://www.ci.chi.il.us/</a>; however, you will easily find other sources, 
  e.g., using a Google image search. Please note: copyright law allows virtually 
  free use of images for school projects.&nbsp; Even in school projects, 
  however, it is good form to credit your image source.&nbsp; Use of others' 
  images without permission in publications or products that are sold is illegal 
  in many cases.</li>
</ul>

